<% layout('layout') -%>
<div class="d-flex">
    <div class="avatar me-5">
        <img src="https://media3.giphy.com/media/GCL3zPUIB7UO4UX01N/giphy.gif?cid=790b76114486c484f0132afde42f16704cde2bd2db2cb6a2&amp;rid=giphy.gif&amp;ct=g"
             alt="Uncanny Animals GIF"
             class="img-fluid"
        />
    </div>
    <div class="flex-fill">
        <h1 class="display-2 fw-bolder"><%= user.username %></h1>

        <p class="text-muted">
            Go to the Applications tab in your developer console, look for the "Cookies" section and verify that
            you have a <span class="fw-bolder">rememberMe</span> entry.
        </p>

        <p class="text-muted">
            The cookie key name along with other variables are customizable when initializing the
            <span class="fw-bolder">RememberMe</span> strategy.
        </p>

        <p class="text-muted pb-5">
            Use the buttons below to test, signin-out keeping the cookie will allow make it so once the page is redirected
            user will still be logged in, the default sign-out will completly destroy the cookie, forcing the user to sign
            back in.
        </p>

        <div class="d-flex">
            <a href="/shallow-sign-out" class="btn btn-lg btn-info me-4 text-white">Sign-Out keeping cookie</a>
            <a href="/sign-out" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary">Sign-Out purging cookie</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>

